casebody.data:
Nevena DASKALOFF v. John L. ZURBRICK, District Director of Immigration. No. 7850. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Nov. 2, 1937. John G. Romanoff, of Detroit, Mich, for appellant. John C. Lehr and Louis M. Hopping, both of Detroit, Mich., for appellee.

Before MOORMAN, HICKS, and SI-MONS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

■ It is ordered that the appeal in this cause be, and the same is, dismissed, pursuant to motion of appellee.
